HEADWORD: Haemochromogen
<hw>Haem`o*chro"mo*gen</hw> <pr>(-kr⟦omac⟧"m⟦osl⟧*j⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Haemochrome</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A body obtained from hemoglobin, by the
action of reducing agents in the absence of oxygen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haemochromometer</ent>⟦br⟧
